# Hybrid Payment Model

CampusChain supports

Ethereum

AND

Razorpay

Both produce the same logical donation.

Payment Method

вҶ“

Verification

вҶ“

Database

вҶ“

Blockchain Proof

вҶ“

Fundraiser Update

---

# Canonical Currency

CampusChain stores fundraising goals in ETH.

Reason

Blockchain operates on Ethereum.

MetaMask uses ETH.

ETH is the immutable source of truth.

Razorpay donations are converted into ETH equivalent for fundraising progress.

Frontend may display INR equivalents for better usability.

---

# Database Layer

TiDB stores

Users

Fundraisers

Donations

Comments

Verification Records

Every successful donation creates a database record before blockchain anchoring.

---

# Blockchain Layer

Purpose

Transparency

Immutability

Auditability

Every verified donation generates

Donation Hash

вҶ“

Ethereum Transaction

вҶ“

Anchor Transaction Hash

вҶ“

Stored in Database

---

# Services Layer

Business logic belongs inside Services.

Example

recordDonation()

Responsible for

Validation

Database Write

Currency Handling

Hash Generation

Anchor Trigger

Controllers should never implement business logic directly.

---

# Middleware Layer

Current Middleware

Authentication

Authorization

Error Handling

Future Middleware

Rate Limiting

Request Logging

Caching

Monitoring

---

# Error Handling

Every layer returns meaningful errors.

Avoid generic

500 Internal Server Error

Instead

Validation Failed

Signature Invalid

Authentication Failed

Database Error

Blockchain Error

